    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE AND FENDERS - IC BUS - DESCRIPTION - SPLASH
        SHIELDS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SPLASH SHIELDS</title>
        <para>Splash shields are part of the fender extensions on the IC BUS. The wheel well openings in the fender
            extensions have been designed to provide splash and spray protection. This protects the lower front of the
            cab from splash and road debris kicked up by the front tires (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900508">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900508" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900508.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 7. IC BUS Fender Extension/Splash Shield</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION (Driver side shown)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
